The paper presents a model set for designing human-robot collaboration experiments, which involves robotics (cs.RO), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), control systems (cs.SY), and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper focuses on the collaborative assembly of furniture, which is a common scenario in HRC, and aims to reduce the amount of work required to set up and reproduce HRC experiments, providing a unified framework to facilitate the comparison and integration of contributions to the field. The paper also provides a set of software libraries for perception, control, and interaction, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.RO and cs.HC, followed by cs.AI, cs.SY, and cs.CV.
